column3: A runtime environment based on a modified version of the Linux kernel and other open source software, designed primarily for touchscreen mobile devices such as smartphones and tablets.
A runtime environment that runs on super computers and uses parallel processing techniques to solve complex computational problems.
A runtime environment that executes in a web browser sandbox, using the browser for user interaction.
An runtime environment created and developed by Apple Inc. exclusively for its hardware that presently powers many of the company's mobile devices, including the iPhone, and iPod Touch.
A family of open source Unix-like runtime environments based on the Linux kernel.
A family of runtime environments developed and marketed by Apple Inc. as the primary operating system for Apple's Mac family of computers.
A family of multitasking, multiuser computer runtime environments that derive from the original AT&T Unix.
A group of graphical runtime environments, all of which are developed, marketed and sold by Microsoft, where each family caters to a certain sector of the computing industry.
A runtime environment created and developed by Apple Inc. for their iPad line of tablet computers.
A runtime environment that allows an application to run as a servlet inside a software container as a component in a web server.
